'''Maia de Carvalho Najla Jabor''' (born 25 September 1915, d. 9 Mar 2001) was a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]] conductor and [[composer]]. She composed concerti and symphonic works, but is best known for sacred songs. She was born and died in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite book |title =Latin American classical composers: a biographical dictionary|first=Miguel|last=Ficher|first2=Martha Furman|last2=Schleifer,|first3=John M.|last3=Furman|publisher=Scarecrow Press|year=2002|accessdate=11 November 2010|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QmdaAAAAMAAJ&q=Najla+Jabor&dq=Najla+Jabor&hl=en&ei=Pn_cTNHnFYiq8AaK7JjRBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAQ}}</ref>
